{{Infobox philosopher |region = [[Western philosophy]] |era = [[Contemporary philosophy|21st-century philosophy]] |color = |image = |name = '''Daniel Stoljar''' |birth_date = 1967 |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |school_tradition = [[Analytic philosophy|Analytic]] | institutions = [[Australian National University]] |main_interests = [[philosophy of mind]], [[metaphysics]], [[metaethics]] | thesis_title = | thesis_url = | thesis_year = | doctoral_advisor = | doctoral_students = |notable_ideas = | spouse = | education = | alma_mater = |influences = |awards = |website = https://sites.google.com/site/danielstoljar/ }}
'''Daniel Stoljar''' (born 1967) is an Australian philosopher and Professor of Philosophy at the [[Australian National University]]. He was the President of the [[Australasian Association of Philosophy]] (2016 - 2017). Stoljar is known for his works on [[physicalism]] and [[philosophical progress]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Montero |first1=Barbara |title=Review of Physicalism |journal=[[Notre Dame Philosophical Reviews]] |date=27 June 2012 |url=https://ndpr.nd.edu/news/physicalism/ |accessdate=7 August 2018 |issn=1538-1617}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=How Philosophy Makes Progress (guest post by Daniel Stoljar) |url=http://dailynous.com/2017/11/07/philosophy-makes-progress-guest-post-daniel-stoljar/ |website=[[Daily Nous]] |accessdate=7 August 2018}}</ref>
==Books== * ''Ignorance and imagination'' (2006) * ''Physicalism'' (2010) * ''Philosophical Progress: In Defence of a Reasonable Optimism'' (2017)
